main event: A civilian observed an oblong-shaped object, the color of an electric light bulb, traveling at high speed over Portland, Oregon on September 10, 1957.
interesting points: The object was described as brighter than the moon, making the moon appear dull in comparison., The object was moving west and disappeared behind a house within seconds., The witness was on their way to work at the Northeast YMCA when they spotted the object., The sighting lasted only a short time, estimated to be just a couple of seconds., The report was submitted to the USAF as part of the Project Blue Book investigation.
witness description: A civilian female working at the Northeast YMCA, who observed the object while walking.
